a contact sport, where a winner has to be declared and injuries are to be expected.

Imagine someone punching you in the stomach 25 times in a row, roughly every two minutes -

Perhaps you were born in the United Kingdom or the United States? Or perhaps somewhere else?

'Tis the season to be jolly,' the old carol goes. Except it may leave you wondering, 'why'?

What do most physicians want? Better trained students. Voluntary choice in training. More intimate/more organic environment. Mastery of psychiatry. Experience. Excellence in training. True responsibility/respect.

This weekend, on April 13 and 14, hundreds of physicians - like me - will convene in London for the Canadian Medical Association (CMA) annual conference.
